summary: carol x reader dealing with reader’s homophobic parents
question: carol x reader dealing with reader’s homophobic parents
answer:
hope this is alright


- you knew your parents didn’t approve of you liking girls

- it upset you, immensely

- after moving out, you fell in love with carol

- she fell in love with you too

- she soothed all your hurt and pain and reminded you that she loved you

- but you missed your parents

- so you asked carol if she would come with you, to see them

- she took your hand, her grasp so gentle, despite what they’re capable of

- “i’ll be your support always”

- that always made you smile

- when you got to the door, you didn’t knock or ring the doorbell

- you couldn’t move

- carol had kept her eye on you the whole car ride over, trying to decipher your thoughts

- she was doing that again

- “we can go, if you want”

- “no i just, need a minute”

- and then the door opened

- your dad

- almost instantly slammed in your face, but carol resisted and kept the door open

- “your daughter has something to say to you” her voice firm, you liked her protective side but put your arm in front of her.

- “it’s okay,” you whispered to her

- you introduced carol as your girlfriend

- your mother came to the door “let her in”

- you turned to carol and frowned, afraid to be alone with them

- “it’s okay i can wait in the car,” she squeeze your hand

- “carol too,”

- and they moved aside letting you both in

- you talked, for the first time in 5 years

- but it didn’t last long

- you couldn’t handle the comments, the tone of voice, it was time to leave

- carol sensed this, and spoke up “i think we better be going,”

- she took you home and you spent the evening, legs entangled between blankets, arms wrapped around each other

- you weren’t ashamed to love her and she knew that

summary: I don't have a problem with people that headcanon Carol Danvers as bi or straight based on her relationship with Rhodey in the...
body:
I don’t have a problem with people that headcanon Carol Danvers as bi or straight based on her relationship with Rhodey in the comics.

I’d just like to see more acknowledgement that comic canon =/= MCU.

MCU Carol may be bi or lesbian or straight. Let people have their headcanons for MCU Carol.
